Dele Ogunyemi and Tukur Muntari The Benin Electricity Distribution Company and Kano Electricity Distribution Company have promised their customers regular power supply amid the lockdown. The BEDC said it had increased electricity supply to its franchise states including Delta, Edo and Ekiti states in a bid to meet the power demand of the customers. The company said it had also commenced the process of boosting the present grid power with additional power supply source. On its part, KEDCO assured its customers across Kano State of regular power supply within the seven days of lockdown in the state. The assurance was contained in a statement by the Head, Corporate Communications of the company, Mr Ibrahim Sani-Shawai, and issued to newsmen in Kano on Thursday. Copyright PUNCH.
